---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="The Pomodoro Technique: 25-Minute Focus Timer Guide" description="The Pomodoro Technique — how 25-minute focused intervals with breaks can help you get more done. Free guide." keywords="pomodoro technique, focus timer, 25 minute timer, productivity method, work intervals, pomodoro breaks, time management technique">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Time</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="The Pomodoro Technique: 25-Minute Focus Timer Guide" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 17, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Struggling with focus? The Pomodoro Technique is one of the simplest and most effective time management methods ever devised. All you need is a timer and the discipline to work in focused 25-minute intervals.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">How It Works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Choose a task</strong> — something specific you want to work on</li>
        <li><strong>Set a timer for 25 minutes</strong> — this is one "pomodoro"</li>
        <li><strong>Work with full focus</strong> — no phone, no email, no distractions</li>
        <li><strong>Stop when the timer rings</strong> — even if you are mid-flow</li>
        <li><strong>Take a 5-minute break</strong> — stand up, stretch, get water</li>
        <li><strong>After 4 pomodoros</strong> — take a longer 15-30 minute break</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Why 25 Minutes?</h2>
      <p>Francesco Cirillo developed this technique in the late 1980s using a tomato-shaped kitchen timer (pomodoro = tomato in Italian). He found that 25 minutes is:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Short enough to feel achievable (anyone can focus for 25 minutes)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Long enough to make real progress on meaningful work</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>A natural fit for most cognitive tasks</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Easy to track and count throughout the day</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">The Science Behind It</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Attention fatigue:</strong> Our ability to concentrate naturally declines after 20-45 minutes</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Urgency effect:</strong> A ticking timer creates gentle pressure that combats procrastination</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Break benefits:</strong> Short breaks allow your brain to consolidate information and reset</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Progress visibility:</strong> Counting completed pomodoros gives a tangible sense of accomplishment</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Tips for Success</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Silence notifications</strong> — put your phone in another room or use airplane mode</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>If interrupted, note it and return</strong> — mark interruptions to understand your patterns</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Adjust the length if needed</strong> — some people prefer 50/10 or 90/20 intervals for deep work</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Plan your pomodoros</strong> — estimate how many a task needs before starting</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Respect the break</strong> — do not skip breaks; they are part of the system</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">What You Can Accomplish in 4 Pomodoros (2 hours)</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Write a 1,500-word article draft</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Complete a chapter of focused study</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Process an email inbox backlog</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Code a small feature or fix several bugs</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Plan an entire project outline</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/tools/reminder" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Timer →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/tools/stopwatch" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Tool →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
